# UJL Clean Code: DRY

## Goal

Avoid repeating the same business rule in multiple places.

## Must

- Centralize shared decision logic (for example insert/paste behavior, can-paste guards, overlay positioning).
- Reuse helpers for repeated transformations and validations.
- Keep one canonical implementation for package boundary rules and public type contracts.

## Should

- Prefer shared test helpers/fixtures over repeated setup blocks.
- Consolidate repeated markup patterns into snippets/components when behavior is identical.

## Avoid

- Copy/paste branches that differ only by small condition changes.
- Parallel implementations for the same state transition.
- Duplicating constants/schema fragments across packages.

## Allowed Exceptions

- Duplicate code temporarily during safe refactors, but remove before merge.
- Small local duplication when abstraction would reduce readability.
